title: Decoding Seduction: Unraveling the Mysteries of Attraction through Film Analysis (Ep 234)
description:
On this episode of Inner Confidence Podcast, host Robbie Kramer discusses the importance of responding to women's emotions instead of just their words, as well as observing body language for signs of confidence and dominance. The podcast offers value from discussing extreme examples of unattractive guys, showcasing three different scenes from movies to demonstrate sexual tension, seduction, and attraction.

Show Notes:

03:11 - "The Aviator" Movie! - watch and learn how to talk to women from Leonardo DiCaprio in this scene! 

05:06: - We discuss "The Aviator" in details - Find out what we can take away from this scene when it comes to talking to women! 

10:08 - "Smile for me just one time" - Will this scene work in a real life scenario? Find out here! 

11:31 - "He didn't say: I want to fuck you!" - How to indirectly tell a woman what you want!

12:45 - "It wouldn't work in this day and age" - Guest shares her thoughts on "The Aviator"

15:07 - "Match point" - Watch and learn from this movie scene! 

17:19 - "I would never react like this" - Guest shares her opinion on the scene!

19:31 - We break down the movie "Match Point" step by step - Figure out these key details that will help you attract woman! 

21:17 - "This is the best way to make your first move" - Realistic example on how to get the first touch from a woman! 

25:20 - "If you're a cheater, you're a cheater!" - Guest shares her thoughts on the characters from: "Match Point"

31:55 - "Realistic? Yes And No!..." - Guest goes in on the scene from "Match Point" 

33:13 - Step by step scene break down! - Learn from the actors! 

36:24 - "Yes And? & No but" - The secret improv technique! Pass her shit test, find out how! 

38:00 - Response Logic VS Emotion! - Know the difference! 

40:43 - Recap from the 3 scenes! - We discuss the movie scenes and what we can take away from them! 

41:35 - "Every guy was so calm" - Learn about confidence!  

43:49 - We discuss similarities between scenes: slow moving, moving with purpose, dominant, eye contact, ..... - Find out more! 

45:42 - I learn a lot from watching movies! - Host explains how he learns from watching movies!

I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife.
